# Appendix L — SLAT for testing

Test cases as SLAT records. Fixtures as SLAT records. Expected vs
actual as SLAT records. When the whole test harness reads and
writes SLATs, tests become part of the substrate.

## A test case

```motoi-scheme
(test-case
  :id        \"parse-post-listing-01\"
  :suite     'intent-parser
  :input     \"post the tulip listing\"
  :context   (context :surface 'shop-dashboard
                       :operator 'alfred)
  :expected  (intent :verb 'post :object 'listing :confidence >0.8)
  :philosopher-lens ((wittgenstein-late \"shop game\")))
```

Head: `test-case`. Notice `:expected` is a partial-match record —
the harness compares field-by-field, allowing predicates like
`>0.8`.

## A fixture

```motoi-scheme
(fixture
  :id           \"shop-alfred-2026-07-12-morning\"
  :operator     'alfred
  :listings     ((listing :sku \"tulip-brooch\"  :status 'active)
                 (listing :sku \"rose-earrings\" :status 'active)
                 (listing :sku \"iris-ring\"     :status 'draft))
  :recent-order '((order :id \"ord-40\" :when \"8:00\" :buyer \"cindy\")))
```

Fixtures are portable. The same fixture can back many tests.

## A test run

```motoi-scheme
(test-run
  :id       \"run-2026-07-12-14-32-01\"
  :suite    'intent-parser
  :started  #inst \"2026-07-12T14:32:01Z\"
  :ended    #inst \"2026-07-12T14:32:44Z\"
  :cases    ((\"parse-post-listing-01\" . pass)
             (\"parse-open-shop-02\"    . pass)
             (\"parse-ambiguous-03\"    . flaky)
             (\"parse-refuse-medical\"  . pass))
  :summary  (:total 4 :pass 3 :flaky 1 :fail 0))
```

Test-run records feed dashboards + Loam projections + regression
tracking.

## Expected vs actual

When a test fails, the record captures the diff:

```motoi-scheme
(test-failure
  :case-id       \"parse-post-listing-01\"
  :expected      (intent :verb 'post :object 'listing :confidence >0.8)
  :actual        (intent :verb 'post :object 'listing :confidence 0.72)
  :diff          '(:confidence-below-threshold 0.72 vs >0.8)
  :suspected     '(surface-detection-drift)
  :incident-narrative \"in-parser-01-004\")
```

Failures become incident narratives (per Book of SLAT ch 14).

## Property tests

```motoi-scheme
(property
  :id       \"roundtrip-utterance\"
  :for-all  (utterance-generator)
  :assert   (lambda (u) (equal? u (slat-read (slat-write u))))
  :iterations 1000)
```

Property tests over generators. When one fails, the failing input
gets minimized and stored as a regression case.

## Golden files

```motoi-scheme
(golden-file
  :test-id       \"render-book-of-words-ch01\"
  :output-path   \"goldens/words-ch01.html\"
  :output-hash   \"sha256:abc...\"
  :updated-at    #inst \"2026-07-12T09:00:00Z\"
  :updated-by    'jess)
```

Golden files anchor renderer output. Any drift shows up in CI.

## the runtime's own regression suite

She runs her own regression suite on her own parses.

```motoi-scheme
(define (self-regression)
  (let* ([conv-docs (recent-conversation-documents 100)]
         [failures  (filter (lambda (d) (not (parse-outcome-ok? d)))
                            conv-docs)])
    (list :ran (length conv-docs)
          :failed (length failures)
          :flag-if (> (length failures) 5))))
```

If more than 5 of the last 100 conversations had parse issues, she
flags it. That's the AI-training-AI shape.

